data.description: A Jewel! 5 Bdrms, 3.5 bath.  Location, location, location. Almost 13 acres ready for horses, livestock or the "Gentleman" Farmer. Pasture has been yielding 30 or more bales of hay. Beautiful Australian Cypress Hardwoods in majority of home; carpet in Guest rooms, ceramic in ktch, baths & mudroom. Public water, with filtration system, purchased by sellers, plus well water available (pump at horse stalls). Solar Panels on roof facing fenced land purchased by seller. Fencing is solar powered as well. Great room has choice of Gas logs or wood burning fireplace.  French doors from Great room lead to deck with spa purchased lately. Large Master Suite with Sitting area, Mbth with  jetted garden tub, separate shower, separate vanities. Home has lots of windows for spectacular "views."  Kitchen is "Cooks" delight with lots of cabinets, solid surface counters + room for dining at the bar (keeping cook company), laundry room, Breakfast room, built in desk and more. Tiled "mud" room has front and rear entry, entry to garage and easy access to" Bonus/ 5th bedroom"(Guest quarters)! Security system in place. Exterior is Hardy Plank. Buffalo Creek runs along right side of property, flood plain on property. I'm sure there is a lot more to tell but I'll bet you want to see for your self! Information taken from county records deemed reliable but not guaranteed. If exact square footage important to buyer, buyer's agent to measure.
